 And the really smart part: remember the principle of Archimedes, the Greek guy with 

00:01:49.770 --> 00:01:55.929
 the bathtub. A floating object moves the same amount of water equal to its weight. An object 

00:01:55.929 --> 00:02:01.100
 that sinks naturally displaces just as much as its volume, but a floating object, like a boat, 

00:02:01.100 --> 00:02:06.219
 displaces as much water as its weight. When they are full of water, those caissons weigh 

00:02:06.219 --> 00:02:12.349
 about 500 tons. If you add one to ten tons of floating boat, ten tons of water will flow 

